      <section id="conclusion">
        <h2>Managing Cortisol Is a Performance Strategy</h2>
        <ContentBox type="tip" title="The Core Insight">
          <p>Cortisol is not your enemy — duration is. Short bursts of cortisol sharpen your brain and mobilize your best performance. Sustained elevation destroys the very cognitive systems you depend on. The highest performers in any demanding field have, consciously or not, mastered the rhythms of stress and recovery. They press hard during bounded periods, then recover fully — not as a reward for working, but as a prerequisite for continuing to work at the highest level. Managing cortisol is not self-care. It is performance architecture.</p>
        </ContentBox>
      </section>

